==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oral
<hw>O"ral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>os</ets>,
<ets>oris</ets>, the mouth, akin to Skr. <ets>⟦amac⟧s</ets>. Cf.
<er>Adore</er>, <er>Orison</er>, <er>Usher</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Uttered by the mouth, or in words; spoken, not written; verbal;
<as>as, <ex>oral</ex> traditions; <ex>oral</ex> testimony; <ex>oral</ex>
law.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the mouth; surrounding or lining
the mouth; <as>as, the <ex>oral</ex> cavity; <ex>oral</ex> cilia or
cirri</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orally</ent>⟦br⟧
